===subject:Americans?
===from:Ramon Yarde
===date:Fri Jun  6 20:57:23 2003
===message:I am sorry but I cannot agree with the notion of America gaining from the Columbian Exchange. As you stated the Native Americans obviously lost the most in the exchange. The Americans of today are mainly descendants of the Europeans that depleted the Native American societies. Therefore I look at them as Europeans still benefiting from the devastation and exploitation of the Americas. If the Americans had truly benefited there would be more Native Americans and other Indian tribes in the USA today.
